<div class="block mb-10 text-[3vw] sm:text-[2.5vw] md:text-[1.7vw] lg:text-[1.4vw] font-thin  font-sans">
    The main pipeline will start from Zawtika Onshore station at Kanbauk village, Yebyu Township, Tanintharyi Region and passing through the sea, Gulf of Mataban and reach the landfall at Daw Nyein village, Pyapon Township, Ayeyarwaddy Region.
                    Then onshore pipeline will receive additional gas supply from Aung Singkha Development Project at this location. Onshore main pipeline will be routed to Yangon and terminated at Gas Distribution Station near Yangon area. Branch pipeline
                    from Junction station will be routed to Power Plant at Kyaiklat Township. The total pipeline length will be approximately 480 km.
</div>